  <text>
    <body>
      <div>
        <hi rendition="#c">
            <head>
                The playing of the world's most famous pianists
                <hi rendition="#larger">
                    <lb/>I. J.
                    <persName type="artist" corresp="https://d-nb.info/gnd/118986724">
                        Paderewski
                    </persName>
                    <lb/>
                    <persName type="artist" corresp="https://d-nb.info/gnd/11918625X">
                        Josef Hofmann
                    </persName>
                </hi>
            </head>
            <lb/>
            <persName type="artist" corresp="https://d-nb.info/gnd/118953915">Carréno</persName>,
            <persName type="artist" corresp="https://d-nb.info/gnd/118518011">Busoni</persName>,
            <persName type="artist" corresp="https://d-nb.info/gnd/118697641">Grieg</persName>,
            <persName type="artist" corresp="https://d-nb.info/gnd/116204400">Bloomfield-Zeisler</persName>,
            and others––
            is reproduced with
            every subtle nuance of shade and expression by
        </hi>
        <lb/>
        <name type="brand">
            <hi rendition="#k">
                The Welte-Mignon<lb/>
                Autograph · Piano
            </hi>
        </name>
        <lb/>
        <hi rendition="#i">
            Recitals at your convenience daily at our Showrooms
        </hi>
      </div>

      <div type="panel">
        <lb/>How <persName type="artist" corresp="https://d-nb.info/gnd/118697641">
          EDVARD GRIEG
        </persName> was Surprised by <persName corresp="https://d-nb.info/gnd/118632892">
          Kaiser Wilhelm II
        </persName>
        <p>
          <lb />When starting on a trip to Norway, the German Emperor ordered a <name type="brand">Welte-
          <lb/>-Mignon Autograph Piano</name> for his steam
          <lb/> yacht. Some recent records made by
          <lb/>
          <persName key="grieg" corresp="https://d-nb.info/gnd/118697641">
            Edvard Grieg
          </persName>
          were included, which
          <lb/>suggested to the Emperor a little
          <lb />pleasantry at the artist’s expense.
        </p>
        <p>
          On arriving at <placeName>Drontheim</placeName>, Grieg was
          <lb />invited on board to meet the Kaiser.
          <lb />In the midst of their conversation the
          <lb />signal was given to render one of
          the Grieg records on the <name type="brand">Welte-Mignon</name>.
        </p>
        <p>
          To the delight of the Kaiser, the
          <lb />maestro instantly recognized his own
          <lb />touch, and after the jest was explained,
          <lb />he had the exquisite
          <lb />pleasure of hearing,
          <lb />for the first time, the
          <lb />outpouring of his
          <lb />own artistic soul.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- First testimonial -->
      <div>
        <quote type="testimonial">
          <q>
            I should not have thought it possible.
            <lb />The Welte-Mignon is, without
            <lb />doubt, the most remarkable
            <lb />musical invention of our age.
          </q>
        </quote>
        <lb/>
        <persName type="artist" corresp="https://d-nb.info/gnd/116020776">
          WALTER DAMROSCH
        </persName>,
        <role>Conductor, New York Symphony Orchestra</role>
      </div>

      <!-- Second testimonial -->
      <div>
        <quote type="testimonial">
          <q>
            The Welte-Mignon is indeed a rescuing
            <lb />invention that renders the great piano
            <lb />virtuoso immortal and his art imper-
            <lb />ishable like the great compositions
            <lb />which he interprets.
          </q>
        </quote>
        <lb/>
        <persName type="artist" corresp="https://d-nb.info/gnd/116753722">
          ALFRED HERTZ
        </persName>,
        <role>Conductor, Metropolitan Opera House Orchestra</role>
      </div>

      <div type="illustration">
        <figure>
          <desc>
            Illustration of a grand piano and a Welte-Mignon push-up.
            Grieg and Wilhelm II. discussing about it.
          </desc>
        </figure>
        <lb/>
        <name type="brand">Welte-Mignon Autograph Piano</name>
        <lb/>
    </div>

      <div>
        <p>
          <name type="brand">Welte-Mignon</name> built in following styles:
          <name type="brand">Welte Piano</name>, with
          <lb />keyboard
          <name type="brand">Welte Piano</name>, with-
          <lb />out keyboard; and
          <name type="brand">Welte
            <lb />Attachment</name> to grand pianos.
        </p>
      </div>

